This paper discusses the challenges of applying machine learning algorithms to large datasets and the use of parallel computing frameworks such as MapReduce, CUDA, and Dryad. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses various ML libraries and tools such as Apache Mahout, GraphLab, and Jubatus, which are related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the impact of cloud computing on the field of ML, which is related to Cloud Computing (cs.CC) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.DB, and cs.SE.
